radiographic_examinations.findings: Endotracheal tube correctly placed; no obvious pulmonary lesions.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT scan of the brain and cervical spine
radiographic_examinations.findings: No intracranial hemorrhage; no fracture of the skull or cervical spine; subgaleal hematoma over the left parietal bone.
Normal aorta; no sign of injury to the liver, kidneys, or spleen.
Hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with asymmetric septal hypertrophy; normal systolic function; mild mitral regurgitation; no dynamic outflow obstruction.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: Study repeated two days later; peak outflow tract gradient at rest was 12 mm Hg, and with Valsalva maneuver it was 15 mm Hg, indicating no provocable gradient.
